results.name: Largest prime with n nonprime substrings (substrings with leading zeros are considered to be nonprime).
link: Hieronymus Fischer, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..25
example: a(0)=373, since 373 is the greatest prime such that all substrings are prime, hence it is the maximal prime with 0 nonprime substrings.
a(3)= 37397, since the nonprime substrings of 37337 are 9, 39 and 7397, and all greater primes have > 3 nonprime substrings.
results.author: _Hieronymus Fischer_, Aug 26 2012
